## Testing plan

All three gates run: `build`, `unit-tests`, `constructor-unit-tests`.

- `build` gate: `OpticalConstructor.Storage` compiles with the four new modules; if ClosedXML is newly added it resolves cleanly; no new C# project introduced.
- `constructor-unit-tests` gate (hosted in `OpticalConstructor.Tests`, the single gated host — NOT a separate `OpticalConstructor.StorageTests` project): the new test files pass and increase the count over the prior baseline.
  - AC-I7/AC-I6 (HistoryTests): a destructive edit followed by `undo` restores `EditHistory.present` to the pre-edit project, a subsequent `redo` restores the edited project, and `undo` on empty history returns the input unchanged; `writeAutosave name project` leaves `<name>.ocproj` unchanged on disk and a distinct `<name>.ocproj.autosave` exists.
  - AC-I8/AC-I10/AC-I11 (ExportImportTests): `exportCsv` writes one header line plus one comma-separated line per row with no solver re-invocation; `importMaterials` reads the `fixtures/sample-nk.csv` refractiveindex.info-style CSV via FSharp.Data and returns `MaterialEntry list`, and `exportMaterials` produces JSON that validates against the `materialEntry` `$def`; `appendRevision` called twice yields two numbered JSON snapshots under `history/` and `diffRevisions` returns a `ProjectDiff` with no external-VCS invocation.
- AC-I9 (export image): `exportChartImage path Png handle` for a Plotly.NET chart is produced by the chart library's own writer — verified at the dispatch boundary (no custom rasterizer in `OpticalConstructor.Storage`); the underlying image render relies on the WebView2/Plotly path and is not asserted headlessly.
- `unit-tests` gate (BerremanTests) stays green (not touched here).

## Risks

- **Medium.** The load-bearing risks: (1) introducing a second JSON stack instead of reusing `serializeProject`'s shared `JsonSerializerOptions` for recent-files/autosave/revisions/material-export (forbidden by §I.5/§I.8 — one stack only); (2) hand-rolling a CSV reader instead of FSharp.Data, or redefining the §D.9 import mapping here (forbidden by §I.8 — own only the file read + `MaterialEntry list` boundary); (3) rasterizing/vectorizing charts or serializing `OpticalConstructorProject` through a sidecar/`.binz` (forbidden — delegate to the chart library's writer; revisions and autosave are JSON). Mitigation: route every persistence path through the slice-003 core, keep `EditHistory` immutable with pattern-matched no-ops (no `.Value`/`.IsSome`), and prove the autosave-distinctness, CSV-shape, import/export, and append/diff invariants by unit test. The `OpticalConstructor.Tests` hosting (not `StorageTests`) is the explicit reconciler decision — do not split out a second test project.

## Hand-off

The [Standard] persistence-II features exist and are unit-tested: recent-files + autosave (`RecentFiles.fs`), whole-project-snapshot undo/redo (`History.fs`), CSV/Excel/image export (`Export.fs`), and the report generator + material-library import/export + design-history/diff (`Report.fs`) — all over the slice-003 storage core, all returning `StorageError` `Result`. The `*.autosave` `.gitignore` entry is added (slice 003 owns the bullet and added `*.binz`). All tests are hosted in `OpticalConstructor.Tests`; no `StorageTests` project was created. Material import consumes the slice-004 `MaterialEntry`/§D.9 mapping boundary; export/report consume the slice-012 `ChartHandle`. Emit the state-of-the-world file with all required ATX headings (`Where we are`, `What's working`, `Tests`, `Architecture`, `Deferred`, `Gotchas`, `Changelog`) and a fenced `gates:` YAML baseline block carrying the updated `constructor-unit-tests` count so the next slice's `count_at_least` gate has a baseline.
